  "inbox.msg1.subject": "Deploy #47 completed successfully",
  "inbox.msg1.preview": "Production v2.4.1 deployed in 1.2s. All healthchecks passed.",
  "inbox.msg1.body": "<p>Deploy <strong>#47</strong> to <code>production</code> completed successfully.</p><p>Version: <code>v2.4.1</code><br>Branch: <code>main</code><br>Time: <code>1.2s</code></p><p>All 142 healthchecks passed. No rollback required.</p>",
  "inbox.msg2.subject": "PR Review: feat/auth-mfa",
  "inbox.msg2.preview": "Review of PR #234. Some points about the MFA implementation...",
  "inbox.msg2.body": "<p>Hey Alex, I reviewed PR <strong>#234</strong> (feat/auth-mfa).</p><p>Overall it looks great, but I have a few points:</p><p>1. <code>generateTOTP()</code> should use <code>crypto.randomBytes</code> instead of <code>Math.random</code>.</p><p>2. The MFA verification middleware needs rate limiting.</p><p>3. Missing a test case for the recovery codes flow.</p><p>Approved with the suggestions above.</p>",
  "inbox.msg3.subject": "Suggestion: Optimize N+1 queries",
  "inbox.msg3.preview": "Detected an N+1 pattern in /api/users that can be optimized...",
  "inbox.msg3.body": "<p>Detected an <strong>N+1 query</strong> pattern in the <code>/api/users</code> endpoint.</p><p>Currently you do:</p><p><code>SELECT * FROM users</code> followed by <code>SELECT * FROM projects WHERE user_id = ?</code> for each user.</p><p>Suggestion: Use a <code>JOIN</code> or <code>DataLoader</code> to batch queries. This would reduce response time from ~120ms to ~15ms.</p><p>Confidence: <strong>94%</strong></p>",
  "inbox.msg4.subject": "Sprint meeting tomorrow",
  "inbox.msg4.preview": "Reminder: Sprint review tomorrow at 10am. Prepare the dashboard demo...",
  "inbox.msg4.body": "<p>Hi Alex!</p><p>Reminder that the sprint review is tomorrow at <strong>10am</strong>.</p><p>Could you prepare the new dashboard demo? The investor will be present.</p><p>Points to cover:</p><p>- Onboarding flow<br>- Dashboard metrics<br>- AI integrations<br>- Deploy pipeline</p>",
  "inbox.msg5.subject": "Build failed: hotfix/css",
  "inbox.msg5.preview": "The hotfix/css branch build failed. Error in PostCSS plugin...",
  "inbox.msg5.body": "<p>The <code>hotfix/css</code> branch build failed.</p><p>Error: <code>PostCSS plugin postcss-custom-properties requires PostCSS 8</code></p><p>Stack trace available in CI Pipeline #889 logs.</p><p>Suggestion: Update <code>postcss</code> to ^8.4.0.</p>",
  "inbox.msg6.subject": "Design tokens updated",
  "inbox.msg6.preview": "Updated the design system tokens. New colors and spacing...",
  "inbox.msg6.body": "<p>Alex, I updated the design tokens in Figma:</p><p>- New semantic colors (success, warning, error)<br>- Updated spacing scale (4px base)<br>- Typography tokens for mobile<br>- Dark mode adjustments</p><p>Already exported to <code>tokens.json</code>. Can you sync?</p>",
  "inbox.msg7.subject": "Vulnerability detected: lodash",
  "inbox.msg7.preview": "CVE-2024-3721 found in lodash@4.17.20. Upgrade recommended.",
  "inbox.msg7.body": "<p>Security vulnerability detected:</p><p><strong>CVE-2024-3721</strong> \u2014 Prototype Pollution in lodash</p><p>Affected package: <code>lodash@4.17.20</code><br>Severity: <strong style=\"color:var(--yellow)\">Medium</strong><br>Fix: Upgrade to <code>lodash@4.17.21</code></p><p>Command: <code>npm update lodash</code></p>",
  "inbox.msg8.subject": "API Gateway: rate limiting",
  "inbox.msg8.preview": "Implemented rate limiting on the gateway. 1000 req/min per IP...",
  "inbox.msg8.body": "<p>Hey Alex, I implemented rate limiting on the API Gateway:</p><p>- 1000 req/min per IP (free tier)<br>- 10000 req/min per API key (pro tier)<br>- 429 response with Retry-After header<br>- Redis-based sliding window</p><p>PR #241 is ready for review.</p>",

